// Adversarial: SpawnPhantom fires on every PerfectBumped, spawning a temporary bolt with
// infinite piercing. Dense layout gives phantoms many cells to pass through. High action_prob
// (0.7) maximises perfect bump attempts, potentially spawning phantoms faster than they expire.
// If phantom despawn on lifespan expiry is missed, BoltCountReasonable fires (cap: 16).
// NoEntityLeaks catches lingering phantom components after the bolt entity is gone.
// NoNaN catches direction corruption when a phantom travels through a just-destroyed cell.
// Stress: 16 runs to explore diverse bump timing and phantom overlap patterns.
(
    breaker: "Aegis",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.7)),
    max_frames: 4000,
    disallowed_failures: [BoltCountReasonable, BoltInBounds, BreakerCountReasonable, BreakerInBounds, NoEntityLeaks, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    invariant_params: (max_bolt_count: 16),
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 3333,
    initial_effects: [
        Stamp(Bolt, When(PerfectBumped, Fire(SpawnPhantom((duration: 2.0, max_active: 3))))),
    ],
)
